Key Match Events: Dodgers pitcher Blake Treinen celebrated after striking out Baltimore’s Gunnar Henderson to get out of a bases-loaded jam in the seventh inning.
The Dodgers became the first club in the majors to reach 80 wins.
Baltimore’s Colton Cowser hammered a 3-and-1 fastball for a three-run homer in the fifth inning.
Evan Phillips picked up his 17th save in a clean ninth inning.
Pre-Game Insights: Dave Roberts mentioned he wouldn’t be managing the Dodgers any differently this week despite the crucial stretch of the season.
Catcher Austin Barnes emphasized the importance of focusing on winning baseball games despite the pressure.
The Dodgers held first baseman Freddie Freeman out of the starting lineup for a third straight game to ease discomfort in his fractured right middle finger.
Post-Match Reflections: Dave Roberts expressed satisfaction with the team's performance, stating, 'I thought we showed well. I don’t think it was a litmus test or anything, but it’s still good to go out there and find ways to win baseball games.'
Blake Treinen reflected on the successful homestand, saying, 'To have a really successful homestand like we had, I think, shows us a lot about ourselves and what we believed we are as a team.'
Mookie Betts commented on the division race, saying, 'Maybe [the division being] close will keep us hungry... It just stays on the whole time. We’ll see.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers' bullpen entered the night with the fourth-best ERA in the majors in August.
Anthony Banda pitched a scoreless sixth inning, lowering his ERA to 2.06.
Blake Treinen inherited a bases-loaded jam in the seventh inning and escaped it with a strikeout of Gunnar Henderson.
Evan Phillips picked up his 17th save in a clean ninth inning.
